{"parentUuid": null, "isSidechain": true, "promptId": "6c3a0b22-aa71-4abe-86b8-7ed7f2e35c75", "agentId": "a1895741286ecf216", "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "Adversarially verify this finding about a design doc (the doc is at /tmp/claude-1000/-home-jleechan-projects-worktree-runner/8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b/scratchpad/gistfile1.txt; the repo is /home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner; you may use WebSearch/WebFetch and read files). Try to REFUTE it. Finding from the \"architecture\" reviewer, severity major:\nTITLE: No security/threat model: per-backend escape surface, docker.sock, egress, fork-PR policy all unaddressed\nDETAIL: For a tool whose entire value proposition is isolation, the design contains no threat model. Unstated: (1) what jobs can reach on the host per backend \u2014 in the plain-Docker fallback, jobs needing docker-in-docker conventionally get /var/run/docker.sock mounted, which is root-equivalent host access, exactly what the tool exists to prevent; the design neither forbids nor addresses it (Sysbox exists to solve this, but the fallback tier skips Sysbox). (2) Network policy: guests presumably get unrestricted egress and, worse, host-LAN access (libvirt default NAT network reaches the host and local network \u2014 metadata endpoints on GCE included, a credential-theft vector). (3) What env/secrets the runner process exposes to jobs. (4) The classic self-hosted footgun: whether these runners may serve public repos / fork PRs, where any drive-by PR gets code execution. Ephemerality mitigates persistence but not exfiltration or lateral movement.\nRECOMMENDATION: Add a security section with a per-backend isolation matrix (what an escaped job reaches). Explicitly: never mount docker.sock in the fallback tier; define guest network policy (block host/LAN/metadata-IP 169.254.169.254 by default, optional egress allowlist); document env hygiene (registration credentials must not be in the job-visible environment \u2014 another argument for JIT config); and make `init` refuse or loudly warn when pointing at a public repo.\nIs the finding factually correct and does the recommendation make sense? If the factual basis is wrong or the severity is inflated, refute it. Default to refuted=true only if you have concrete contrary evidence or the claim is unsupported after checking."}, "uuid": "03899076-f49a-4445-b6cd-3757422abf45", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T22:00:27.999Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner", "sessionId": "8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b", "version": "2.1.198", "gitBranch": "fix/linux-runner-pre-job-hook", "slug": "velvet-wishing-cake"}
